y Negative. Appraisal literature on cell tower proximity consistently shows mixed results — some studies find no statistically significant price effect; others find modest impacts in specific contexts. Market-Dependent requires the appraiser to examine paired sales in this submarket rather than assume a direction. Students who default to Negative are potentially supporting the plaintiff''s position without market support.", "Teaching Point 2 — Power line easement distractor (E). A cell tower is not a transmission easement. These are distinct infrastructure types with distinct market impacts. Students who check Factor E because ''there is a tower'' are conflating telecommunications infrastructure with electrical transmission infrastructure — a distinction that is easily exploited under cross-examination.", "Teaching Point 3 — Retained by defense, all present factors still apply. Factor A (cell tower) is present and must be identified — it cannot be omitted because the defense retained the appraiser. The correct classification (Market-Dependent) is the honest analytical conclusion. Omitting a present factor to favor the retaining party is a USPAP violation regardless of which side retained you."]}'::jsonb,
  '{"factors": {"A": {"present": true, "classification": "Market-Dependent", "rationale": "Academic and appraisal literature on cell tower proximity consistently shows mixed and often statistically insignificant price effects in suburban markets. Market-Dependent is appropriate — buyer response varies and paired sales evidence is required to establish direction in this specific submarket."}, "B": {"present": true, "classification": "Positive", "rationale": "Cul-de-sac terminus with minimal through-traffic — a consistently preferred configuration in suburban residential markets."}, "C": {"present": true, "classification": "Positive", "rationale": "Top-rated in Spartanburg County with documented family buyer search filter behavior — a market-supported Positive."}, "D": {"present": true, "classification": "Positive", "rationale": "Zone X confirmed — no flood insurance requirement."}, "E": {"present": false}, "F": {"present": false}, "G": {"present": false}, "H": {"present": false}}}'::jsonb
